      "id": 194317,
      "postNumber": 2,
      "createdAt": "2024-07-22T09:43:28.631Z",
      "author": "dvdsmpsn (David @ David Simpson Apps)",
      "cookedHtml": "<p>The subitem is in a different board to it’s parent. All subitems are in a separate board. That’s why they can have different columns.</p>\n<p>You need to query the board id of the subitem before using the <code>change_simple_column_value</code> mutation.</p>\n<p>In the example below, the <code>boardId</code> is <code>1518439140</code>:</p>\n<p></p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/original/3X/4/0/4077a20a1ad7b998722adcdfe70022663c6ca7eb.png\" title=\"Screenshot 2024-07-22 at 13.40.02\"><img src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/optimized/3X/4/0/4077a20a1ad7b998722adcdfe70022663c6ca7eb_2_513x499.png\" alt=\"Screenshot 2024-07-22 at 13.40.02\" width=\"513\" height=\"499\" /><div class=\"meta\"><span class=\"filename\">Screenshot 2024-07-22 at 13.40.02</span><span class=\"informations\">1702×1658 438 KB</span></div></a></div><p></p>\n<p>…but the <code>boardId</code> of the subitem is actually <code>1572248940</code>, whereas the <code>boardId</code> of it’s parent is as expected:</p>\n<p></p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/original/3X/3/c/3c950caa08be3123ac0d401bea610c0adab74934.png\" title=\"Screenshot 2024-07-22 at 13.45.57\"><img src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/optimized/3X/3/c/3c950caa08be3123ac0d401bea610c0adab74934_2_690x321.png\" alt=\"Screenshot 2024-07-22 at 13.45.57\" width=\"690\" height=\"321\" /><div class=\"meta\"><span class=\"filename\">Screenshot 2024-07-22 at 13.45.57</span><span class=\"informations\">1604×748 51.4 KB</span></div></a></div><p></p>"
    },
